What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: No, don't take it. Find any way you can to get out of taking this ultimately useless 5 hour lab class on Monday evenings. But you probably can't because as an ABET ChemE major you have to take boring, irrelevant, and yet time consuming classes like this.

The TAs are fun. You will get to leave before 9 about half of the time, mostly at the beginning of the semester - the bio labs take longer than the chemistry labs. And yeah, learn some biology. But really this class isn't scary.
